{
  "description": "A close-up, symmetrical view into the center of a vibrant red tulip. The petals are a warm, soft red with subtle variations in tone. At the very center are six dark, almost black, anthers surrounding a pale yellow, elongated stigma. The anthers have a dusting of pollen, visible as tiny specks. The petals curve inward towards the center, creating a tunnel-like effect. The image is sharp and detailed, capturing the delicate texture of the flower's reproductive parts.",
